# Schemas and template contracts

## Source of truth

- **Recommended fields per report type:** `schemas/report_profiles.json` — all **7** profiles: `phase1_alberta`, `phase1_devon`, `phase2_esa`, `groundwater_monitoring`, `reclamation_certificate`, `phase3_remediation`, `template_driven`.
- **Legacy / AI tagger alignment:** `schemas/field_contract.json` — sync with profile DWDA fields; AI tagger uses `get_recommended_fields(report_type)` for all profiles.

## Key schema files

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `report_profiles.json` | Profiles, `recommended_fields`, `sheet_mappings`, `appendix_templates` |
| `field_contract.json` | Legacy ProjectData + sheet row fields |
| `sed002_phase1_checklist.json` | SED 002 §10 preflight |
| `dwda_compliance_checklist.json` | Directive 050 / DWDA checklist |
| `ecoventure_dwda_cell_contract.json` | Ecoventure xltm cell ingest (`contract_version`) |
| `dwda_salt_additives.json` | Salt additive factors for calc engine |
| `project_folder.json` | `project.json` layout (`ecoventure_workbook_filename`) |
| `phase2_esa_checklist.json`, `groundwater_checklist.json`, `reclamation_checklist.json` | Vertical profile preflight |

## Excel layout

- **`ProjectData`**: row 1 = headers (→ snake_case keys), **row 2+ = one site per row** (batch: all rows or pick one in UI).
- **DWDA sheets:** `DwdaChecklist`, `DwdaCalculations` (see [docs/21-dwda-directive-050-compliance.md](docs/21-dwda-directive-050-compliance.md)).
- **Groundwater:** `MonitoringWells`, `WaterLevels`, `GroundwaterLab`, `FieldNotes`.
- Sheet names are **case-sensitive** — see [EXCEL_LAYOUT.txt](EXCEL_LAYOUT.txt) and the always-on architecture rule.

## Word templates

- Each `{{ variable }}` in **one** formatting run (no split bold inside a tag).
- Tables: **static header row**, then `{%tr for item in lab_results %}`, then `{%tr endfor %}` — [JINJA2_CHEATSHEET.txt](JINJA2_CHEATSHEET.txt).
- Phase 2 lab tables: prefer **`result_display`** (RichText exceedances); **`result_plain`** for plain text.

## Pre-flight semantics

- **Missing template vars** → warn, render empty (do not block).
- **Invalid files / required sheets missing / split tags** → block generation.

When adding production fields: extend **`report_profiles.json`** first; sync **`field_contract.json`** for AI tagger; run `tests/test_schema_parity.py`.
